      <description>&lt;div id=&#34;outline-container-headline-1&#34; class=&#34;outline-2&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;headline-1&#34;&gt;&#xA;Website&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div id=&#34;outline-text-headline-1&#34; class=&#34;outline-text-2&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The website for the nursery is implemented using the &lt;a href=&#34;https://gohugo.io/&#34;&gt;Hugo website generator&lt;/a&gt;, using my own &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/computer-instruction-sets/hugo-personal-website-theme&#34;&gt;theme&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xA;This section has subsections for:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;The &lt;a href=&#34;#hugo-configuration&#34;&gt;configuration file&lt;/a&gt; that Hugo and my theme use.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Some of the pages on that website. They&amp;#39;re exported from their &lt;a href=&#34;https://code.cyberearth.systems/emsenn/personal-website&#34;&gt;Org-mode source file&lt;/a&gt; into Hugo-compatible Markdown using &lt;a href=&#34;https://ox-hugo.scripter.co&#34;&gt;Ox-Hugo&lt;/a&gt;. Additional pages, like those for my writing, are created by using Ox-Hugo on the appropriate Org-mode file.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Local data, such as an array of my recent activities or upcoming plans.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This doc is largely just the content and configuration - to see how it is used, you&amp;#39;ll want to look at the &lt;a href=&#34;https://emsenn.net/computer-instruction-sets/hugo-personal-website-theme/&#34;&gt;theme documentation&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
